5:
Long story short, the academy has
no records of anyone named "Gram"
working there.
8:
The current headmistress is a
downright terrifying lady named
Nihilyana Voluntas—the same last
name, right? Figured I'd ask her.
11:
You should have seen the look she
gave me—she's got one expressive
face, that lady. Anyway, she didn't
so much as say a single word... Just
pointed at the ground.
15: The Dark Mage of the Kaleidoscope...
19:
Bingo. I'm hoping he'll show up soon
to give us a grand tour of the place.
30:
I asked you a question! Are you hard
of hearing, boy?
35:
N-no. It's just, I... have no idea what
you're talking about.
41:
I'm talking about what you did with
SHIBUYA, you fool!
52:
I'd heard you were capable of such
feats, but... I never thought you'd do
something THAT absurd—and with
no thought as to the consequences!
55:
The shifts are growing wilder by the
day! The Kaleidoscope is RIDDLED
with holes, voices are whispering
from every corner—AND the
dragon's power yet waxes!
59:
It's horrible! Every single conceivable
thing that could go wrong DID, and
it's all because of—
64:
Wait. You spoke of a dragon just
now. To what do you refer?
67:
I've heard that you all saw the
Dragon's Iris—the colossal eye that
appeared over Shibuya—and that it
led to people awakening to new
powers.
71:
The truth is, I saw the Iris on that day
as well, though I did so via the
Dracostream in which Orochi was
sealed.
78:
Yes, the Dracostream... That would
be the reincarnation pathway of the
ancient dragons.
83:
Indeed. It was that which gave
people the power to change reality
itself. If you ask me, that's far more
terrifying than anything I've heard
about these "Overlords."
86:
Tell me, what do you know of the
Dragon's Iris?
91:
The Origin Dragon...
The source of all magic, capable
even of seeing the Void.
94:
But so what? None of that changes
anything about my present
predicament!
97:
My invention has run amok, and
those damn voices won't shut up!
Before long, its countless writhing
hands will seize the dragon in their
grasp...
102:
You look like you're in a lot of
distress.
108:
No need to be circuitous about it.
You need our help, don't you?
114:
Help?! From YOU? Don't make me
laugh. You're the ones who caused
this whole wretched mess!
117:
Not only did you poke holes in my
Kaleidoscope, connecting it to
distant worlds, but now you've
straight up gone and STITCHED a
world onto ours!
122: Yeah... He definitely needs our help.
133:
We'll do what we can to make this
right.
136:
We've got a lot of allies who would
be willing to lend a hand. However...
we'd also like something from you in
return.
141:
You're quite fast on the uptake, Alk. I
didn't even need to spell it out for
you.
150:
What could you possibly hope to
accomplish now? It's far too late!
153:
Hah! Look at this petty little doormat
of a man. He hasn't changed an iota
after all these years.
156:
And so hideously desperate too!
Why else would he make sure to
write "Voluntas" in nice big letters on
his invitation?
160:
So you did follow us after all. Could
have done us the basic courtesy of
saying something, Nihilyana. I'm not
a fan of being followed.
164:
Do you really think that
overdramatic, self-indulgent worm
would have come crawling out of
his hole if he knew I'd be here?
175:
Nihilyana... Wait a minute. The one
from Voluntas Academy?
181:
Haha! Precisely. Nihilyana
Voluntas—headmistress of the
Arcane Arts Academy of the very
same name—at your service.
184:
And while I'm doing introductions, I
suppose I should mention that the
whiny little turd stain over there is
my ex-husband.
198: I can kind of see it.
